Implementation of a Pomodoro Timer application using Java's Swing library. The application features 
dynamic timer intervals for focused work. Integrates an intuitive graphical user interface with start, 
pause, and timer reset functionalities. Incorporates a state management system to seamlessly transition 
between work and break periods, adhering to the Pomodoro Technique. Employed color-coded visual cues 
for different timer phases, enhancing user experience. 
